    <main class="container pb-5">
        <section class="mb-5">
            <h2 class="mb-3">What is this?</h2>
            <p>The SwordFight API provides pre-calculated outcomes for every possible move combination in the SwordFight game engine. All outcomes are deterministic and pre-generated as static JSON files.</p>

            <p>This API is:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Stateless</strong> - No server-side computation, just file lookups</li>
                <li><strong>Fast</strong> - Served from CDN, cached indefinitely</li>
                <li><strong>Open Source</strong> - Built with the <a href="https://github.com/MWDelaney/swordfight.engine">SwordFight Engine</a></li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-5">
            <h2 class="mb-3">Quick Start</h2>

            <p><strong>Get all characters:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>fetch('https://api.swordfight.me/characters/index.json')
  .then(r => r.json())
  .then(data => console.log(data.characters));</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Get a specific character:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>fetch('https://api.swordfight.me/characters/human-fighter.json')
  .then(r => r.json())
  .then(character => console.log(character));</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Get a round outcome:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>fetch('https://api.swordfight.me/rounds/human-fighter/goblin/24/30.json')
  .then(r => r.json())
  .then(outcome => console.log(outcome));</code></pre>
        </section>

